claims:
35. A method of preparing a conjugate of Neisseria meningitidis serogroup X capsular polysaccharide and a carrier molecule selected from the group consisting of
a. (i) oxidizing a primary hydroxyl group in the capsular polysaccharide resulting in an oxidized polysaccharide comprising an aldehyde group; and
(ii) coupling the oxidized polysaccharide to a carrier protein via the aldehyde group to produce the conjugate;
b. (i) reductive amination of the reducing terminus of the capsular polysaccharide resulting in a modified polysaccharide with a primary amine group bonded to the C-1 atom of the terminal subunit by a covalent bond; and
(ii) coupling the modified polysaccharide to the carrier molecule via the primary amine group to produce the conjugate; and

c. (i) reduction of the reducing terminus of the capsular polysaccharide resulting in a modified polysaccharide comprising two vicinal hydroxyl groups at that terminus;
(ii) oxidative cleavage of the vicinal hydroxyl groups resulting in a further modified polysaccharide with an aldehyde group at the terminus;
(iii) reductive amination of the aldehyde group resulting in a further modified polysaccharide with a primary amine group at the terminus; and
(iv) coupling the further modified polysaccharide to a carrier molecule via the primary amine group to produce the conjugate.
